Additionally, but not specific to L&T leadership they included:


taking an active interest in people, giving advice and support to help them achieve their academic goals (S2-Q18);



leading by example—being effective in their work;



being available (S2-Q19);



being generous with their time and expertise (S2-Q19).

It is interesting that this group could not clearly identify individuals who fitted this model and felt that the university did not provide a culture to support such leaders partly due to the individualistic culture and the lack of consideration of the role of leader.
